<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Meets Visiting Chrysler Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401124294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1218 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1401124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 14 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Li Lanqing met with a delegation from U.S. Chrysler Corporation 
here this afternoon. 
  The delegation, led by Peter C. Badore, director-general of 
the Asian-Pacific region of the Chrysler's International 
Department, came to celebrate the 10th anniversary of the 
Beijing Jeep Corporation, Ltd (BJC), which was the first 
Sino-foreign joint- venture in China's automotive industry. 
  Li said that BJC has made marked achievements since it was 
inaugurated in January 1984. 
  He expressed the hope that the corporation will continue to 
enlarge its production scale, enhance its ability of developing 
new products and raise its localization rate so as to bring more 
competitive products into the third country markets. 
  Over the past 10 years, BJC has turned out a total of 
350,000 
automobiles. The localization rate of its Cherokee has up to 
date exceeded 60 percent. 

</TEXT>

