<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Auto Industry Shows `Increase' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1201073394 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1201073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] Shandong Province has succeeded in improving its 
auto industry to a new level thanks to vigorously readjusting 
the mix of products, introducing advanced technologies from 
foreign countries, and setting up technical and economic 
associations with fraternal provinces. In 1993 the province 
realized a total output of 7.68 billion yuan, which showed a 38 
percent increase over 1992 and realized 740 million yuan of 
profits and taxes, which showed a 46 percent increase over 1992. 
The sale rate of products reached more than 95 percent. During 
the year, the province turned out 176 varieties of new products. 
Of these varieties, four reached the world standard; 11 filled 
the national gaps in this regard; and 35 reached the national 
advanced standards. The rate of output value of these new 
products reached 31.7 percent which surpasses that of 1992 by 10 
percent. 

</TEXT>

