<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Secretary on Agricultural, Rural Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1301141094 Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1301141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] A Henan provincial economic work meeting opened 
in Zhengzhou yesterday. Provincial Party Secretary Li Changchun 
made an important speech at the opening ceremony. 
  He stressed: We should take the decision of the Third 
Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee as guidance, 
conscientiously implement central policies and measures on 
strengthening agricultural and rural economic development, 
persist in taking agriculture as the foundation in the course of 
establishing the socialist market economic structure, actively 
orient enteprises toward the market, and speed up the pace of 
making the people prosperous. 
  The opening ceremony was presided over by Governor Ma 
Zhongchen. [passage omitted] 
  In his speech, Li Changchun first analyzed the province's 
current agricultural and rural situation. He said: Following 
the deepening of reform in the 1990's, Henan's economy has 
entered a new development period. Agriculture has started 
transforming from a single type of cultivation structure into an 
overall aspect embracing agriculture, forestry, animal 
husbandry, sideline production, and fisheries. Industry, 
commerce, construction, and transportation are are undergoing 
comprehensive transformation. The rural economy is developing 
from the small-peasant economy into an open socialist market 
economy. Most peasants are beginning to move toward moderate 
prosperity after resolving the problem of adequate food and 
clothing. New vitality and vigor are emerging in the entire 
agriculture and rural economy. In the last three years, grain 
output has remained at more than 30 billion kg and stood at 35.3 
billion kg last year, a record high in history. The output of 
cotton, tobacco, and oil-bearing crops has remained stable. 
Forestry, animal husbandry, sideline production, and fisheries 
have seen comparatively great development. After topping 100 
billion yuan in 1992, the gross output value of township and 
town enterprises throughout the province continued to grow in 
1993 and was expected to reach 195 billion yuan, an increase of 
62.5 percent over the previous year. In 1993 the peasant per 
capita net income was estimated at 660 yuan, an increase of 133 
yuan over 1990. 
  He pointed out: We must soberly understand that prominent 
problems obstructing the province's agricultural and rural 
economic development have not been fundamentally resolved. New 
contradictions and problems have emerged in rural reform, 
opening up, and economic development. Peasant income increases 
slowly, the rural socialized service system is imperfect, 
agricultural investment is inadequate, agriculture is not strong 
at resisting natural disasters, there are many instable factors 
in rural areas, peasant burdens have not been fundamentally 
resolved, and the situation in the social order is grim. 
[passage omitted] 
  In conclusion, Li Changchun pointed out: Henan is a big 
agricultural province, in which agriculture and the rural 
economy play a decisive role in entire national economic and 
social development. There is a need to strengthen party 
leadership over rural work to bring about faster and better 
development in the rural economy. Leading cadres at all levels 
should constantly improve their work style and work methods, 
strengthen their study and investigation, and enhance their 
leadership level. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

