<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Continues Visits Eritrea </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets President </H4>
<F P=102> OW1301203594 Beijing XINHUA in English 2014 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Asmara, January 13 (XINHUA) -- Eritrean President 
Isayas Afewerki held friendly talks here today with visiting 
Chinese Vice- Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen . 
  During the talks, Afewerki said Qian's visit is an 
indication 
of the importance China attaches to Eritrea and to the friendly 
relations between the two countries. 
  The Eritrean Government pursues the policy of enhancing 
cooperation with China in various fields, the president 
stressed, saying the cooperation is in the interest of the 
Eritrean people and helps promote peace and development of 
Africa. 
  Eritrea is now facing the task of full-scale reconstruction 
after 30 years of war and it expects assistance from China, the 
president added. 
  Qian conveyed to Afewerki the greetings of Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng. He told Afewerki that Jiang 
expects him to visit China at an early date so that the 
bilateral relations be pushed to a higher level. 
  The Chinese vice-premier said the trade and economic 
cooperation between the two countries has had a good start 
following the establishment of diplomatic ties months ago. 
  It is in the interest of the two peoples that the Chinese 
Government and Eritrean Government work together to enhance 
mutual exchanges and bilateral cooperation, Qian stressed. 
  Afewerki briefed Qian on the situation in the horn of 
Africa. 
He said maintenance of the regional peace, together with 
development of economy and elimination of poverty and 
backwardness, are the major tasks facing Eritrea. 
  The two leaders agreed that the development of economy is 
the 
basis of solutions to many problems in the African continent. 

</TEXT>

