<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Legal Rights for `Overseas Chinese' Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401125294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1152 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1401125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 14 (XINHUA) -- Legal rights of 
returned overseas Chinese and the relatives of overseas Chinese 
in Beijing will be better protected thanks to the new 
regulations approved by the Standing Committee of the Municipal 
People's Congress today. 
  The new regulations embody the principles of the national 
law 
on this subject outlined in June last year. 
  The city has now got a population of 250,000 returned 
overseas Chinese and their relatives. Seven out of ten 
joint-venture enterprises in the capital are funded by overseas 
Chinese and Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan compatriots. 
  The regulations confirm that the returned overseas Chinese 
and their relatives have rights to take part in social, 
political and economic activities and to get proper education 
and visit their relatives abroad. They are also ensured of 
their rights in dealing with personal property. 
  The regulations go into detail on the issue of the private 
houses, one of the greatest concerns of the returned overseas 
Chinese and their relatives, and formulate some preferential 
policies for them. 
  The regulations have outlined a number of special policies 
to 
encourage the returned overseas Chinese and their relatives to 
set up enterprises in their motherland. 

</TEXT>

