<H3> <TI>   More `Experts' Granted Government Allowances </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1401143394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1328 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1401143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 14 (XINHUA) -- Another 50,000 
specialists, scholars and technicians have been selected to 
receive special government allowances for their marked 
contributions last year, according to officials with the 
Ministry of Personnel. 
  China began to grant special government allowances to 
outstanding experts in 1990. By the end of last year, nearly 
110,000 experts had been granted allowances. 
  Compared to those selected before, there are more young 
people among those selected this time, and many of them are 
engaged closely in agriculture, industry and technological 
popularization. 
  The officials said the allowance program helps encourage 
hard 
working people and thus intensifies people's respect for 
knowledge and professionally capable personnel. 
  The state will continue to carry out the program with the 
improvement of relevant regulations and concrete measures, the 
officials said. 

</TEXT>

