<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group To Gather Information on NAFTA Markets </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301044894 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1301044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] In order to assist domestic manufacturers to enter 
markets of the North American Free Trade Agreement, or NAFTA, 
the Economic Ministry has formed a fact-finding mission to the 
region. The ministry has already decided upon four areas in 
Mexico to assist Taiwan manufacturers in setting up investment 
and factories. The NAFTA formally went into effect at the 
beginning of this year. Due to the advantageous position of 
Mexico, the ministry has decided to put focus on developing 
markets in that country. The ministry's Investment Commission, 
the China External Trade Development Council, and the Chinese 
Chamber of Commerce in Mexico jointly held the fact- finding 
mission and selected the areas most suited to the needs of local 
manufacturers. The ministry will hold forums explaining the 
investment targets in Taipei and Taichung over the next several 
days, as well as introducing the NAFTA and the effects of it on 
Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

