<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin, Zhang Meet PLA Art Delegates </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301134194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1313 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 13 (XINHUA) -- Jiang Zemin, Chinese 
president and general secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Chinese Communist Party, today met with the delegates to the Art 
Working Conference of the People's Liberation Army (PLA). 
  Jiang, also chairman of the Central Military Commission, 
said, "Our art is people's art and socialist art, and its 
position and function are very important." 
  He said that successful art work can become spiritual 
strength to promote reforms and development, for it can improve 
people's morality and aesthetic judgment, and encourage people 
to work hard to revitalize China. 
  Before the meeting, Jiang had cordial talks with senior 
writers and artists of the PLA. 
  Zhang Zhen, vice-chairman of the Central Military 
Commission, 
and other leaders of the commission, were present during the 
meeting. 

