<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guizhou Secretary Addresses United Front Work Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1801103094 Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1801103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guiyang Guizhou People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Addressing a provincial meeting on united front 
work which closed the day before yesterday, provincial party 
committee Secretary Liu Fangren emphasized: As far as the 
united front work is concerned, we in this province should 
follow the guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory on 
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, give full play 
to those basic social functions exclusive to united front work, 
make use of every positive factor, unite with all the forces 
that can be united, and do our share to consolidate and promote 
the great solidarity among all the nationalities of this 
province and to fulfill the province's second- stage strategic 
goal for the 1990's. 
  Liu Fangren pointed out that the province at present should 
devote great efforts to the following aspects with regard to 
united front work: 
  1. It is necessary to uphold and perfect the multi-party 
cooperation and political consultation system under the CPC's 
leadership, and to do a really good job in fostering, selecting, 
appointing, and employing non-CPC personalities. Party 
committees, governments, and organs concerned at all levels must 
wholeheartedly and effectively serve democratic parties and 
other non-CPC personalities in all circles and help them solve 
actual problems. 
  2. It is necessary to work really hard to win the support of 
representative personalities of the nonpublic economic sector, 
with a view to promoting the development of the non-state-owned 
economy in the province. 
  3. It is necessary to attach great importance to nationality 
and religious affairs. Party committees and governments at all 
levels must take the initiative in selecting, fostering, and 
employing cadres from minority nationalities in accordance with 
the guideline laid down in the documents concerned issued by the 
central authorities. To do a good job in handling religious 
affairs, all localities must comprehensively implement the 
party's policy toward religions and should do a better job in 
safeguarding normal religious activities. At the same time, all 
localities must make greater efforts to do a still better job in 
united front work abroad, to extend the united front, to unite 
with the vast number of Taiwan compatriots, Hong Kong and Macao 
compatriots, and overseas Chinese, thus contributing to the 
economic development of the province. 
  In his speech, Liu Fangren demanded that party committees at 
all levels strengthen leadership over united front work, really 
attach great importance to united front work, and place it on 
important agenda, thus making greater contributions to the 
economic prosperity of the province. 

</TEXT>

