<F P=100> United States &amp; Canada </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Repatriates 123 Illegal Immigrants to Xiamen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1801055794 Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO in Chinese 18 Jan 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> HK1801055794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Special dispatch: "123 Illegal Emigrants Will be </F>
Repatriated From the United States to Xiamen Today"] 
  [Text] Xiamen, 17 Jan (TA KUNG PAO)--U.S. immigration 
authorities will repatriate a group of Chinese illegal 
immigrants to China directly from Los Angeles by plane tomorrow 
(18 January); it is expected that the plane will land at 
Xiamen's Gaoqi International Airport at about 1400. 
  A relevant person disclosed here that about 123 Chinese 
illegal immigrants will be repatriated, among them most are 
peasants from Fujian Province's Fuzhou City and Changle County, 
and one of them may be a Cantonese. 
  U.S. immigration authorities have hired a special plane this 
time and appointed three officials to escort the illegal 
immigrants to China to handle repatriation formalities. There 
will also be 130 security personnel on board the plane. 
  Last year, the U.S. side repatriated a group of Chinese 
illegal immigrants, and the destination was Xiamen. However, 
unlike the repatriation last time, the plane will fly directly 
to China after taking off from the United States, without making 
a detour. 
  Originally, the repatriation work had been scheduled for 15 
January, but was changed to 18 January for some reason. This 
afternoon, the relevant authorities of Fujian Province and 
Xiamen city convened a meeting again to make arrangements for 
the concrete matters of repatriation and reception tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

