<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Radio on Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK1701125494 Beijing China Radio International in Korean 
1100 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1701125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Comrade Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC 
Central Committee and Chinese president, met with Comrade Hwang 
Chang-yop, secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea Central 
Committee, this morning in Beijing. During the meeting, he said 
that China, as always, would make every effort to continuously 
strengthen and develop the traditional friendship between China 
and Korea and strengthen exchange and cooperation between the 
two countries in various fields. 
  Comrade Jiang Zemin also said that the CPC always very much 
treasures the traditional friendship between China and Korea and 
is persistently making efforts to constantly strengthen and 
develop the relations of friendship and cooperation between the 
two countries. He also said that the traditional friendship 
between the two countries, the two parties, and the two peoples 
was founded and fostered by leaders of the old generation of the 
two countries and sealed with blood by the peoples of the two 
countries. 
  Comrade Hwang Chang-yop praised the brilliant achievements 
the Chinese people have brought about in building socialism with 
Chinese characteristics. He also said that the Korean people 
regard these achievements by the Chinese people as their own and 
are boundlessly pleased with them. He wished that the Chinese 
people would bring about greater achievements under the 
leadership of the CPC, with Comrade Jiang Zemin as its core. 
  Comrade Hwang Chang-yop asked Comrade Jiang Zemin to convey 
President Kim Il-song's greetings to Comrade Deng Xiaoping. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

