<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Government Delegation Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ranariddh, Hun Sen Arrive </H4>
<F P=102> OW1701084294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0751 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1701084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 17 (XINHUA) -- At the invitation of 
Chinese Premier Li Peng, a delegation from the Government of the 
Kingdom of Cambodia led by First Prime Minister Norodom 
Ranariddh and Second Prime Minister Hun Sen arrived here this 
afternoon on a five-day official visit to China. 
  This is the first visit to China by the two prime ministers 
since Cambodia resumed peace and formed its new government. 
  Among those greeting them at the airport were She Jianming, 
chairman of the Chinese Government Reception Committee and vice- 
minister of the State Planning Commission, and Chinese 
Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan. 

</TEXT>

