<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Government Delegation Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Jiang Receives Prime Ministers </H4>
<F P=102> OW1801125594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1243 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1801125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 18 (XINHUA) -- China will continue 
to provide assistance within its capability for Cambodia for its 
restoration and reconstruction, said President Jiang Zemin here 
today when he met with a visiting Cambodian Government 
delegation. 
  The delegation from the Kingdom of Cambodia, led by First 
Prime Minister Samdech Norodom Ranariddh and Second Prime 
Minister Hun Sen, arrived here yesterday on an official visit. 
  Ranariddh thanked China for its aid to Cambodia, on behalf 
of 
the Cambodian Government. 
  Jiang said the visit by the two prime ministers showed that 
the Cambodian Government pays much attention to its friendly and 
cooperative relations with China. 
  The visit, a great event in bilateral relations, will 
promote 
mutual understanding and friendship, Jiang said. 
  Ranariddh said his delegation held fruitful talks with 
Premier Li Peng yesterday, and hoped that the visit would 
further consolidate and improve Sino-Cambodian relations. 
  Jiang said that Cambodia's transition from a 20-year-long 
war 
to a period of peaceful reconstruction brought light to the 
Cambodian people's common will and was also in line with the 
major trend of peace and development in the region. 
  Jiang said the Chinese Government sincerely hopes that the 
Cambodian Government will cherish the hard-won peace, further 
advance the process of national reconciliation and mobilize all 
the Cambodian people to build up their country. 
  Ranariddh said that though facing difficulties, the 
Cambodians are optimistic about their future. 
  Under the leadership of King Norodom Sihanouk, they will 
build Cambodia into a country of independence, sovereignty, 
territorial integrity and prosperity, Ranariddh added. 
  Jiang described King Sihanouk as the beloved leader of the 
Cambodian people and respected friend of the Chinese people, 
adding that he had made indelible contributions to Cambodia's 
independence. 
  Earlier today, the Cambodian guests laid a wreath at the 
Monument to the People's Heroes and paid their respects to the 
remains of Chairman Mao Zedong. They also inspected two 
factories in Beijing. 
  They are scheduled to visit the Hainan island province in 
south China tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

