<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Departs for Visit to Three Nations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1601060394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0551 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1601060394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 16 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman 
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress 
(NPC), left here today by a special plane for a 15-day official 
goodwill visit to three West European nations. 
  The three nations are Germany, Switzerland and Austria. It 
will be the first visit of Chinese NPC chairman to West European 
nations. 
  Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the 
Political 
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party 
and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference, went to see the NPC chairman 
off this morning in the Great Hall of the People. 
  Qiao's entourage includes his wife Yu Wen, Cao Zhi, 
secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee, Ye Gongqi, 
chairman of the Standing Committee of the Shanghai Municipal 
People's Congress, Raidi, chairman of the Standing Committee of 
the Tibet Autonomous Regional People's Congress, Dai Jie, member 
of the NPC Standing Committee and vice-chairman of the NPC 
Financial and Economic Committee, and Jiang Enzhu, vice-minister 
of foreign affairs. 
  Also present at the send-off ceremony were NPC Vice-Chairmen 
Tian Jiyun, Wang Hanbin and Li Peiyao as well as the three 
nation's ambassadors to China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

