<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlin Officials Host Reception </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1601230194 Beijing XINHUA in English 2229 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1601230194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin, January 16 (XINHUA) -- A senior German 
official said here this evening that the visit to Germany by 
Qiao Shi, China's National People's Congress (NPC) Standing 
Committee, will strengthen Germany-China relationship. 
  Hanna-Rnate Laurien, president of the Berlin City's 
parliament, made these remarks at a reception hosted by her in 
honor of Qiao Shi, who is here on an eight-day official goodwill 
visit to Germany. 
  She said she was very pleased that Qiao's visit is paid 
following the China visits respectively by German Chancellor 
Helmut Kohl last year and mayor of Berlin City Eberhatd Diepgen 
in 1988. 
  Laurien hailed the sound growth of bilateral ties in 
economy, 
science and culture. 
  She said Germany's investment in China ranks the sixth in 
the 
world, adding that there is a sign that such position will be 
moved forward. 
  Qiao said Berlin, the largest city in Germany, has great 
influence on the world. 
  With the German Federal Government and parliament to be 
moved 
to Berlin before the end of this century, the city will play 
more important roles in the country's politics, economy and 
cultural life, he said. 
  "We are particularly pleased to note that Berlin and China 
have shared very close relationship," he added. 
  Their links in every aspect are daily increasing and areas 
for cooperation become wider, he said. 
  Qiao hoped that "such relationship will be further developed 
with fruitful results," Qiao said. 
  Among those present were Qiao Shi's wife Yu Wen and Cao Zhi, 
secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee, who are 
accompanying Qiao on the visit. 
  Before the reception, Qiao met and had a friendly talk with 
Laurien here. 

</TEXT>

