<H3> <TI>   Qiao Meets Mayor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1801155594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1429 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1801155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg, January 18 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, visiting 
chairman of China's National People's Congress (NPC) Standing 
Committee, met and had friendly talks with Mayor of Hamburg 
Henning Voscherau here this morning. 
  Qiao said relations between China and Germany have always 
been good. Following Chancellor Helmut Kohl's visit to China 
last year, bilateral ties have entered a stage of all-round 
development, he added. 
  "I believe that with the growth of bilateral ties, the 
relationship between China and Hamburg will be further 
enhanced," he said. 
  Voscherau said the people of hamburg are looking with 
admiration at China's successful reform and opening up in the 
past 15 years. 
  With the development of China, he said, relations between 
the 
two countries will grow smoothly. 
  Extending his warm welcome to the Chinese guests, he said 
Qiao's visit to Germany shows bilateral ties have been further 
strengthened. 
  Qiao, his wife and entourage arrived here yesterday evening 
from Berlin. 

</TEXT>

