<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Issue $1 Billion in Bonds in U.S. </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1501144494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1415 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1501144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 15 (XINHUA) -- China's Ministry of 
Finance has registered in the Securities Exchange Commission of 
the United States to issue one billion U.S. dollars-worth of 
global bonds. 
  Led by Merrill Lynch and Co., Inc., some world major 
security 
companies and banks will underwrite the bonds in the United 
States, Europe and Asia. 
  Jin Renqing, China's deputy finance minister, said that this 
was the first time for the Chinese Government to issue global 
bonds and enter the U.S. capital market. 

</TEXT>

