<H3> <TI>   Fujian Encourages Investment From Taiwan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1801055694 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1801055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a news briefing yesterday, a person in charge of 
the provincial government's Taiwan affairs office indicated that 
this year Fujian will further widen the scope of opening up and 
work hard to scale a new height in Fujian-Taiwan economic and 
trade cooperation. He said that all levels of Taiwan affairs 
offices in the province will continue to act as bridges and 
links in encouraging big financial groups and enterprises to 
invest in Fujian. He welcomed Taiwan businessmen to invest in 
the construction of highways, power stations, harbors, airports, 
and other basic facilities. He also encouraged them to invest 
in Fujian's hinterland areas. 
  He also indicated that in the course of helping Taiwan 
businessmen run enterprises in Fujian, the provincial Taiwan 
affairs office will cooperate with the relevant departments in 
strengthening Taiwan-related local legislation. 

</TEXT>

