<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Arrives in Sudan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301214294 Beijing XINHUA in English 2126 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, January 13 (XINHUA) -- Chinese 
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived in 
Khartoum today on a three-day official visit. 
  He said upon arrival at the Khartoum International Airport 
that China and Sudan have strong, traditional and friendly ties. 
These friendly relations have been strengthened and developed 
in the 35 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations 
between them. 
  He said he will meet with Sudanese leaders and have talks 
with Foreign Minister Husayn Abu-Salih on bilateral relations 
and international issues of common interest. 
  His talks will also deal with the situation in the region, 
he 
said, expressing his confidence that his current visit will 
contribute to increasing friendship and understanding between 
the two peoples and enhancing cooperation between them. 
  Sudan is the third leg of Qian's six-nation African tour. He 
has visited Ethiopia and Eritrea and will continue on to Kenya, 
Madagascar and Mauritius. 

</TEXT>

