<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Activities of Jilin's He Zhukang Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Attends Large Enterprise Forum </H4>
<F P=102> SK1601035194 Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1601035194 </F>
<F P=104>  Changchun Jilin People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] How can the state-owned large and medium-sized 
enterprises further change their managerial mechanisms, overcome 
their current difficulties, free themselves from difficulties as 
soon as possible, or enter markets? On 15 January, the 
provincial party committee and the provincial government 
cosponsored a forum to explore new ways for enlivening 
state-owned large and medium-sized enterprises and solving the 
problems in these aspects. 
  Eleven examples, including Liaoyuan (Jiancheng) machinery 
plant, the Jilin chemical fiber corporation, the Hunchun gold 
mine, and the Jilin (Fengyuan) cement plant, introduced their 
experience in reforming the wage system and the property right 
system, developing various forms of management system, 
optimizing the industrial structure and the product mix, and 
accepting the challenges on domestic and international markets. 
  Provincial Leaders He Zhukang, Gao Yan, Wang Jinshan, Liu 
Xilin, Feng Ximing, Liu Yazhi, and Wang Guofa conscientiously 
heard the speeches made by these examples. Present at the forum 
were vice mayors of the city, prefectural, and autonomous 
prefectural governments in charge of the industrial work; 
chairmen of the city, prefectural, and autonomous prefectural 
planning and economic commissions and restructuring commissions; 
directors and managers of the units that introduced their 
experience at the forum and relevant enterprises; and 
responsible comrades of the provincial-level departments 
concerned. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-45339 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi011_s_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
