<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Liu Huaqing's Visit to Indonesia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Received by Defense Minister </H4>
<F P=102> OW1501135494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1300 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1501135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, January 15 (XINHUA) -- General Liu Huaqing, 
visiting vice chairman of the Central Military Commission of 
China, called on General (ret) [retired] Edi Sudrajat, 
Indonesian minister of defense and security here today. 
  Minister Sudrajat extended warm welcome to Vice Chairman Liu 
Huaqing for his visit to Indonesia, saying that the visit is of 
great significance, ushering in a new stage in the 
Sino-Indonesian relations. He wished the friendly relations 
between the two countries to further strengthen in the future. 
  Vice Chairman Liu Huaqing briefed the host on the state of 
affairs of China's economic construction and Army's building up, 
as well as China's suggestions and stands for cooperation in the 
Asian and Pacific region. Liu Huaqing said that both China and 
Indonesia are countries with economic construction as center 
task. Therefore, they need a permanent and stable international 
peaceful environment for their construction. 
  Vice Chairman Liu Huaqing and his party today also laid a 
wreath at the national heroes cemetery of Indonesia. 

</TEXT>

