<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Liu Huaqing's Visit to Indonesia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visits Bandung, Returns to Jakarta </H4>
<F P=102> OW1701162094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1548 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1701162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, January 17 (XINHUA) -- General Liu 
Huaqing, vice chairman of the Central Military Commission of 
China, and his entourage today visited Bandung, the third 
biggest city in Indonesia, 180 kilometers away from Jakarta. 
  Upon arrival at bandung's Husein Sastranegara Air Force 
Base, 
the Chinese guests were welcomed by Major General Muzani Syukur, 
commander of Military Area Command III/Wiliwangi, and Major 
General Rukman Saminudin, chief of state police, West Java 
Region. 
  Then the visiting vice chairman and his entourage paid a 
visit to the Musantara Aircraft Industry (in short term, IPTN), 
the only company in Indonesia to produce aircraft. 
  In keen interests, Vice Chairman Liu listened to a brief 
introduction and toured several workshops. 
  They also visited the museum of the Asian, African 
conference. 
  Wife of Vice Chairman Liu, Madame Xu Hongxia, this morning 
visited the famous beautiful Indonesia in Miniature Park and 
attended a bamboo music performance in the afternoon in Bandung. 
  Vice Chairman Liu and his entourage returned to Jakarta 
later 
today. 

</TEXT>

